TEXTO_AYUDA_1_CENTROS_TRABAJO: If the checkbox "Affects all Work Centers" (it is the checkbox on the left of the company) at the level of each company is selected, you will have access to all the Work Centers of the company. If new work centers are added to the companies in the future, the user will see the data of these new work centers by default. To make modifications, you will need to uncheck the checkbox and then select the "Modify centers" button. Pressing the button will show the Work Centers of the selected company. By checking or unchecking the checkboxes for each Work Center, you can select which one you want to access and which one you do not want to access.
TEXTO_AYUDA_2_CENTROS_TRABAJO: If the checkbox "Affects all Work Centers" (it is the checkbox on the left of the company) at the level of each company is NOT selected, you will only have access to selected Work Centers on the right side of the screen. If new work centers are added to the companies in the future, the user will NOT see the data of these new work centers by default. To make modifications, you must select the "Modify centers" button. Pressing the button will show the Work Centers of the selected company. By checking or unchecking the checkboxes for each Work Center, you can select which one you want to access and which one you do not want to access.
TEXTO_AYUDA_3_CENTROS_TRABAJO: If you want to see the Work Centers associated with the user, you must select the "View Centers" button. Pressing the button will display the Work Centers of the selected company in read-only mode.
TEXTO_AYUDA_4_CENTROS_TRABAJO: By default, active data will be displayed, but inactive data can also be displayed.
